00:04:11.950 --> 00:04:14.650 align:middle line:84%
>> I was on the cardiovascular
anesthesia service,

00:04:14.650 --> 00:04:18.100 align:middle line:84%
and day after day, I was putting
people to sleep and watching

00:04:18.100 --> 00:04:20.950 align:middle line:84%
surgeons open their chest and
pull out-- there's yellow,

00:04:20.950 --> 00:04:24.750 align:middle line:84%
greasy gobs of material that
was clogging up their arteries

00:04:24.750 --> 00:04:26.593 align:middle line:90%
called atherosclerosis.

00:04:26.593 --> 00:04:28.510 align:middle line:84%
And one day, I was
watching a surgeon pull out

00:04:28.510 --> 00:04:30.560 align:middle line:90%
of slithery yellow piece.

00:04:30.560 --> 00:04:32.120 align:middle line:84%
And I thought to
myself, my heavens.

00:04:32.120 --> 00:04:33.750 align:middle line:90%
That looks like chicken fat.

00:04:33.750 --> 00:04:35.495 align:middle line:84%
And a little voice
on my shoulder

00:04:35.495 --> 00:04:38.950 align:middle line:84%
said, there's a good reason
why it looks like chicken fat.

00:04:38.950 --> 00:04:42.130 align:middle line:84%
It is chicken fat and
cow fat and pig fat

00:04:42.130 --> 00:04:45.190 align:middle line:84%
and the fat of every
other slow animal that

00:04:45.190 --> 00:04:46.870 align:middle line:84%
was walking past
this man's table

00:04:46.870 --> 00:04:49.080 align:middle line:90%
when he had a fork in his hand.

00:04:49.080 --> 00:04:52.580 align:middle line:84%
And I realized that
my patient's diet

00:04:52.580 --> 00:04:55.030 align:middle line:84%
was playing a major role
in what was putting them

00:04:55.030 --> 00:04:56.880 align:middle line:90%
on the operating table.

00:04:56.880 --> 00:05:01.480 align:middle line:84%
And I was very concerned
because I had a father who

00:05:01.480 --> 00:05:02.860 align:middle line:90%
died of clogged arteries.

00:05:02.860 --> 00:05:05.230 align:middle line:84%
I had his genetics, and I
knew that I was probably

00:05:05.230 --> 00:05:06.730 align:middle line:84%
going to be laying
on that operating

00:05:06.730 --> 00:05:09.520 align:middle line:84%
table with that Stryker
saw going up my sternum.

00:05:09.520 --> 00:05:12.610 align:middle line:84%
And I said, I don't
want that to happen.

00:05:12.610 --> 00:05:15.940 align:middle line:84%
As I changed to a whole
food, plant-based diet,

00:05:15.940 --> 00:05:22.370 align:middle line:84%
a 10 kilogram band of fat
around my waist melted away.

00:05:22.370 --> 00:05:25.030 align:middle line:84%
My blood pressure had
been elevated at 150-90.

00:05:25.030 --> 00:05:27.040 align:middle line:84%
That settled down
to 110 over 70.

00:05:27.040 --> 00:05:29.145 align:middle line:84%
My cholesterol
dropped 20 points,

00:05:29.145 --> 00:05:31.900 align:middle line:84%
and I felt great waking up
in a nice, lean, light body

00:05:31.900 --> 00:05:32.720 align:middle line:90%
every day.

00:05:32.720 --> 00:05:35.980 align:middle line:84%
And I knew that
food was absolutely

00:05:35.980 --> 00:05:39.610 align:middle line:90%
key in creating a healthy body.

00:05:39.610 --> 00:05:43.240 align:middle line:84%
Well, here I was as an
anesthesia resident literally

00:05:43.240 --> 00:05:45.340 align:middle line:84%
putting people to
sleep all day, and I

00:05:45.340 --> 00:05:48.420 align:middle line:84%
started feeling like
a cog in the machine.

00:05:48.420 --> 00:05:51.670 align:middle line:84%
You know, next,
next, and no one was

00:05:51.670 --> 00:05:53.260 align:middle line:84%
talking to these
people about what

00:05:53.260 --> 00:05:56.060 align:middle line:84%
it was that was clogging
up their arteries.

00:05:56.060 --> 00:05:58.970 align:middle line:84%
And I couldn't be complicit
in that any longer.

00:05:58.970 --> 00:06:02.230 align:middle line:84%
And as much as I
enjoyed anesthesia,

00:06:02.230 --> 00:06:05.020 align:middle line:84%
I knew I didn't want to spend
my time putting people to sleep.

00:06:05.020 --> 00:06:08.590 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to go back to general
practice and help them wake up.

00:06:08.590 --> 00:06:12.700 align:middle line:84%
So I returned back to general
practice in suburban Vancouver.

00:06:12.700 --> 00:06:17.020 align:middle line:84%
And this time, I was
empowered because the patients

00:06:17.020 --> 00:06:20.950 align:middle line:84%
that I had originally seen day
after day in my office that

00:06:20.950 --> 00:06:23.650 align:middle line:84%
made me feel just
dreadful and impotent--

00:06:23.650 --> 00:06:27.040 align:middle line:84%
the overweight fellow with high
blood pressure and diabetes

00:06:27.040 --> 00:06:28.240 align:middle line:90%
and clogged arteries.

00:06:28.240 --> 00:06:29.920 align:middle line:84%
I didn't really know
what to tell them.

00:06:29.920 --> 00:06:31.990 align:middle line:84%
I would fiddle with
their insulin dosage

00:06:31.990 --> 00:06:34.570 align:middle line:84%
and say, you ought to
lose some weight, Joe.

00:06:34.570 --> 00:06:36.420 align:middle line:84%
But I really didn't
know what to say.

00:06:36.420 --> 00:06:38.770 align:middle line:90%
Now, I knew what to say.

00:06:38.770 --> 00:06:43.000 align:middle line:84%
Stop running all that animal
fat and animal protein

00:06:43.000 --> 00:06:45.700 align:middle line:84%
and processed foods
through your bloodstream,

00:06:45.700 --> 00:06:48.160 align:middle line:84%
and get on a whole
food, plant-based diet.

00:06:48.160 --> 00:06:52.300 align:middle line:84%
I had a friend nearby who
was an excellent vegan chef,

00:06:52.300 --> 00:06:55.570 align:middle line:84%
and I would send them to her
where she would give them

00:06:55.570 --> 00:06:56.890 align:middle line:90%
cooking lessons.

00:06:56.890 --> 00:06:59.020 align:middle line:84%
And lo and behold, the
same wonderful changes

00:06:59.020 --> 00:07:00.970 align:middle line:84%
began happening in
my patients' bodies.

00:07:00.970 --> 00:07:01.990 align:middle line:90%
They became leaner.

00:07:01.990 --> 00:07:04.030 align:middle line:84%
Their high blood
pressures went down.

00:07:04.030 --> 00:07:06.790 align:middle line:90%
Their diabetes went away.

00:07:06.790 --> 00:07:10.480 align:middle line:84%
And this was very startling for
me because in medical school,

00:07:10.480 --> 00:07:13.300 align:middle line:84%
I had learned that with
your diabetic patients,

00:07:13.300 --> 00:07:15.100 align:middle line:84%
once on insulin,
always on insulin.

00:07:15.100 --> 00:07:16.923 align:middle line:90%
No one gets off insulin.

00:07:16.923 --> 00:07:19.090 align:middle line:84%
And when you treat someone
with high blood pressure,

00:07:19.090 --> 00:07:21.173 align:middle line:84%
they will take these pills
the rest of their life.

00:07:21.173 --> 00:07:23.540 align:middle line:90%
This is lifetime medication.

00:07:23.540 --> 00:07:25.270 align:middle line:84%
Well, I was finding
not only could I

00:07:25.270 --> 00:07:26.920 align:middle line:84%
get these people off
their medication,

00:07:26.920 --> 00:07:28.270 align:middle line:90%
I had to get them off.

00:07:28.270 --> 00:07:30.190 align:middle line:84%
The patients with
high blood pressure

00:07:30.190 --> 00:07:32.920 align:middle line:84%
and these powerful medications
that dilated their blood

00:07:32.920 --> 00:07:36.190 align:middle line:84%
vessels and slowed down their
heartbeat-- they'd stand up,

00:07:36.190 --> 00:07:38.560 align:middle line:84%
their blood pressure would
drop, they would pass out,

00:07:38.560 --> 00:07:41.260 align:middle line:84%
and you have to get them
off the medications.

00:07:41.260 --> 00:07:43.720 align:middle line:84%
And the same thing with the
diabetic patients-- their blood

00:07:43.720 --> 00:07:44.650 align:middle line:90%
sugars would drop.

00:07:44.650 --> 00:07:46.600 align:middle line:84%
You have to stop their
insulin, or they'll

00:07:46.600 --> 00:07:49.060 align:middle line:90%
have hypoglycemic reactions.

00:07:49.060 --> 00:07:51.250 align:middle line:84%
I remember the first
time I told a patient

00:07:51.250 --> 00:07:53.712 align:middle line:84%
to stop your blood
pressure medications,

00:07:53.712 --> 00:07:55.420 align:middle line:84%
I thought there would
be a puff of smoke,

00:07:55.420 --> 00:07:57.790 align:middle line:84%
and the ghost of my
internal medicine professor

00:07:57.790 --> 00:07:59.980 align:middle line:84%
would appear and say,
what did you say?

00:07:59.980 --> 00:08:02.410 align:middle line:84%
Stop his high blood
pressure medication?

00:08:02.410 --> 00:08:03.598 align:middle line:90%
Hand in your stethoscope.

00:08:03.598 --> 00:08:04.640 align:middle line:90%
Take off your white coat.

00:08:04.640 --> 00:08:06.280 align:middle line:90%
You're no longer a doctor.

00:08:06.280 --> 00:08:07.690 align:middle line:90%
But the truth is--

00:08:07.690 --> 00:08:11.180 align:middle line:84%
I realize that their
dogma that they had

00:08:11.180 --> 00:08:15.460 align:middle line:84%
have been teach me-- that
was where the untruth lie.

00:08:15.460 --> 00:08:19.000 align:middle line:84%
And they were blinded by
the pharmacological model

00:08:19.000 --> 00:08:21.400 align:middle line:84%
of Western medicine,
that the only treatment

00:08:21.400 --> 00:08:25.570 align:middle line:84%
is genetic for these
unknown-cause diseases.

00:08:25.570 --> 00:08:28.510 align:middle line:84%
But the truth is, the
cause isn't unknown.

00:08:28.510 --> 00:08:29.830 align:middle line:90%
It's the food.

00:08:29.830 --> 00:08:33.171 align:middle line:90%
It's what the people are eating.

