00:34:11.000 --> 00:34:12.210 align:middle line:90%
I have to write for them.

00:34:12.210 --> 00:34:14.420 align:middle line:84%
So I think it's time
to really reconsider

00:34:14.420 --> 00:34:17.219 align:middle line:84%
the role of dairy products
in the human diet.

00:34:17.219 --> 00:34:22.170 align:middle line:84%
>> We also tend to use the
television as our sole source

00:34:22.170 --> 00:34:25.600 align:middle line:84%
of health and
nutritional information.

00:34:25.600 --> 00:34:29.520 align:middle line:84%
Remembering that that
information is provided

00:34:29.520 --> 00:34:33.300 align:middle line:84%
by the companies
selling the products,

00:34:33.300 --> 00:34:37.620 align:middle line:84%
and the thing that
drives television

00:34:37.620 --> 00:34:40.960 align:middle line:90%
is advertisement dollars.

00:34:40.960 --> 00:34:43.780 align:middle line:90%
Take dairy, for instance.

00:34:43.780 --> 00:34:46.719 align:middle line:84%
Before the advent
of television, dairy

00:34:46.719 --> 00:34:52.600 align:middle line:84%
wasn't consumed by us for a
need to increase our calcium.

00:34:52.600 --> 00:34:56.110 align:middle line:84%
Dairy was merely a product
that was available to us

00:34:56.110 --> 00:34:58.560 align:middle line:84%
that we used in
most of our recipes

00:34:58.560 --> 00:35:00.610 align:middle line:90%
and in our day-to-day lives.

00:35:00.610 --> 00:35:04.040 align:middle line:84%
Then came the
television commercials

00:35:04.040 --> 00:35:08.620 align:middle line:84%
that told us we need to consume
dairy for our daily calcium

00:35:08.620 --> 00:35:10.090 align:middle line:90%
intake.

00:35:10.090 --> 00:35:15.520 align:middle line:84%
The question is, then, if we
have only been farming animals

00:35:15.520 --> 00:35:19.660 align:middle line:84%
for around 12,000 years, what
did we do for our calcium

00:35:19.660 --> 00:35:25.490 align:middle line:84%
intake for the millions of
years of our human evolution?

00:35:25.490 --> 00:35:29.330 align:middle line:84%
What did we do for our
daily calcium intake

00:35:29.330 --> 00:35:33.350 align:middle line:84%
before we had cows to
milk and televisions

00:35:33.350 --> 00:35:35.780 align:middle line:90%
to tell us that we needed it?

00:35:35.780 --> 00:35:40.820 align:middle line:84%
So if milk is a perfect,
natural source of calcium,

00:35:40.820 --> 00:35:45.260 align:middle line:84%
why are a lot of companies
now adding calcium to milk?

00:35:45.260 --> 00:35:49.760 align:middle line:84%
Because when we ingest
milk or dairy products,

00:35:49.760 --> 00:35:53.870 align:middle line:84%
it causes our body to become
acidic, and as a buffer

00:35:53.870 --> 00:35:58.850 align:middle line:84%
to restore the pH
back in our bodies,

00:35:58.850 --> 00:36:01.790 align:middle line:84%
our bodies draw
calcium carbonate

00:36:01.790 --> 00:36:03.410 align:middle line:90%
to restore the equilibrium.

00:36:03.410 --> 00:36:08.680 align:middle line:84%
And the only place we can
draw calcium carbonate from

00:36:08.680 --> 00:36:10.310 align:middle line:90%
is our bones.

00:36:10.310 --> 00:36:15.530 align:middle line:84%
So in actual fact, the
consumption of dairy products

00:36:15.530 --> 00:36:19.190 align:middle line:84%
is leaching calcium
from our bones.

00:36:19.190 --> 00:36:22.820 align:middle line:84%
The evidence is now showing
us that the countries who

00:36:22.820 --> 00:36:27.200 align:middle line:84%
consume the most dairy
are suffering the highest

00:36:27.200 --> 00:36:30.930 align:middle line:90%
rates of osteoporosis.

00:36:30.930 --> 00:36:34.970 align:middle line:84%
So if it was true that the
more dairy we consumed,

00:36:34.970 --> 00:36:37.460 align:middle line:84%
the less osteoporosis
we would get,

00:36:37.460 --> 00:36:40.040 align:middle line:84%
we would see the
opposite figures.

00:36:40.040 --> 00:36:41.330 align:middle line:90%
But we're not.

00:36:41.330 --> 00:36:44.630 align:middle line:84%
So if we could ask ourself,
if we didn't have television

00:36:44.630 --> 00:36:47.780 align:middle line:84%
to tell us that we
needed to drink milk,

00:36:47.780 --> 00:36:51.050 align:middle line:84%
what would we use to
determine whether we

00:36:51.050 --> 00:36:53.210 align:middle line:90%
should be drinking milk or not?

00:36:53.210 --> 00:36:58.160 align:middle line:84%
The answer is, we would
use our own common sense.

00:36:58.160 --> 00:37:03.340 align:middle line:84%
So as human beings, once we
have weaned off our own mother's

00:37:03.340 --> 00:37:06.670 align:middle line:84%
milk and begun solid
food, we actually

00:37:06.670 --> 00:37:11.020 align:middle line:84%
lose the enzyme in our gut
that allows us to break down

00:37:11.020 --> 00:37:14.510 align:middle line:90%
casein, the protein in milk.

00:37:14.510 --> 00:37:21.820 align:middle line:84%
So from that point onwards,
we have no more requirement

00:37:21.820 --> 00:37:25.490 align:middle line:84%
for our mother's milk for
the rest of our lives.

00:37:25.490 --> 00:37:31.270 align:middle line:84%
We don't then go looking
to include in our diet

00:37:31.270 --> 00:37:34.450 align:middle line:90%
the milk from another animal.

00:37:34.450 --> 00:37:37.570 align:middle line:84%
In fact, naturally, we
wouldn't go looking for it

00:37:37.570 --> 00:37:41.260 align:middle line:84%
at all until we turn
on the television,

00:37:41.260 --> 00:37:44.800 align:middle line:84%
and a company tells
you that you need

00:37:44.800 --> 00:37:49.490 align:middle line:84%
to take the milk of a cow
for the rest of your life.

00:37:49.490 --> 00:37:52.210 align:middle line:84%
So we should also
use our common sense

00:37:52.210 --> 00:37:56.540 align:middle line:84%
when people use the
argument of time

00:37:56.540 --> 00:38:00.620 align:middle line:84%
to justify us continuing
to do things that we've

00:38:00.620 --> 00:38:03.770 align:middle line:90%
done for a long length of time.

00:38:03.770 --> 00:38:07.880 align:middle line:84%
People say that we've
eaten meat and drank dairy

00:38:07.880 --> 00:38:09.840 align:middle line:90%
for thousands of years.

00:38:09.840 --> 00:38:17.390 align:middle line:84%
But the same is true of
smoking tobacco and turning

00:38:17.390 --> 00:38:21.020 align:middle line:90%
poppy flowers into opium.

00:38:21.020 --> 00:38:25.370 align:middle line:84%
In fact, doing something that is
harmful to our health for such

00:38:25.370 --> 00:38:30.260 align:middle line:84%
a long period of time
unfortunately just shows us

00:38:30.260 --> 00:38:33.557 align:middle line:90%
that we are very slow learners.

