00:42:30.160 --> 00:42:35.070 align:middle line:84%
>> So at this point, I
became fascinated with

00:42:35.070 --> 00:42:40.500 align:middle line:84%
the commonly-held medical
belief that genes controlled

00:42:40.500 --> 00:42:44.410 align:middle line:84%
everything, and that's
the common held belief

00:42:44.410 --> 00:42:45.720 align:middle line:90%
for the general public.

00:42:45.720 --> 00:42:52.170 align:middle line:84%
Now, this then led me
into my own study of what

00:42:52.170 --> 00:42:56.320 align:middle line:90%
is now known as epigenetics--

00:42:56.320 --> 00:43:00.720 align:middle line:84%
epigenetics meaning
control above the genes.

00:43:00.720 --> 00:43:05.700 align:middle line:84%
People that I've studied
like Dr. Bruce Lipton

00:43:05.700 --> 00:43:09.450 align:middle line:84%
say that this is
completely untrue.

00:43:09.450 --> 00:43:12.540 align:middle line:84%
He taught in
universities, lectured

00:43:12.540 --> 00:43:17.820 align:middle line:84%
on the subject of genes
controlling everything

00:43:17.820 --> 00:43:19.180 align:middle line:90%
for 40-odd years.

00:43:19.180 --> 00:43:24.480 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Lipton is quoted as
saying genes cause nothing.

00:43:24.480 --> 00:43:29.610 align:middle line:84%
They are no more than
blueprints for building blocks,

00:43:29.610 --> 00:43:33.700 align:middle line:84%
and blueprints do not
have on and off switches.

00:43:33.700 --> 00:43:38.660 align:middle line:84%
In fact, he says that the
principle element for life

00:43:38.660 --> 00:43:40.080 align:middle line:90%
are proteins.

00:43:40.080 --> 00:43:42.660 align:middle line:84%
The cells of your
body are made up

00:43:42.660 --> 00:43:48.090 align:middle line:84%
of more than 150,000
proteins, and protein in Latin

00:43:48.090 --> 00:43:51.180 align:middle line:90%
means primary particle.

00:43:51.180 --> 00:43:55.530 align:middle line:84%
In fact, the very
basics of life is

00:43:55.530 --> 00:44:01.200 align:middle line:84%
that proteins can change
shape, and they do so

00:44:01.200 --> 00:44:04.740 align:middle line:84%
by responding to
external signals.

00:44:04.740 --> 00:44:07.530 align:middle line:84%
And these signals are
coming from the environment

00:44:07.530 --> 00:44:10.020 align:middle line:84%
that they are placed
in, and they are

00:44:10.020 --> 00:44:13.080 align:middle line:90%
called confirmational changes.

00:44:13.080 --> 00:44:18.480 align:middle line:84%
In short, you are just a
protein machine responding

00:44:18.480 --> 00:44:20.910 align:middle line:90%
to environmental changes.

00:44:20.910 --> 00:44:23.790 align:middle line:84%
Now, around 40 years
ago, while Dr. Lipton

00:44:23.790 --> 00:44:27.480 align:middle line:84%
was doing his studies
on stem cell research,

00:44:27.480 --> 00:44:30.450 align:middle line:84%
he was cloning
stem cells, and he

00:44:30.450 --> 00:44:33.690 align:middle line:84%
put one stem cell
in a Petri dish,

00:44:33.690 --> 00:44:39.370 align:middle line:84%
and the cells split, replicate
every 10 to 12 hours.

00:44:39.370 --> 00:44:45.390 align:middle line:84%
And within a week, he has 50,000
stem cells in the Petri dish.

00:44:45.390 --> 00:44:47.940 align:middle line:84%
And remember that each
one of those cells

00:44:47.940 --> 00:44:51.100 align:middle line:90%
is absolutely identical.

00:44:51.100 --> 00:44:54.230 align:middle line:84%
It is an exact replica
of the other cell.

00:44:54.230 --> 00:44:58.500 align:middle line:84%
He then, after a week,
split these 50,000 cells

00:44:58.500 --> 00:45:02.110 align:middle line:84%
into three separate
Petri dishes,

00:45:02.110 --> 00:45:03.930 align:middle line:84%
and the only thing
he did differently

00:45:03.930 --> 00:45:08.580 align:middle line:84%
was change the chemistry
of the medium in which they

00:45:08.580 --> 00:45:09.960 align:middle line:90%
were growing in.

00:45:09.960 --> 00:45:15.060 align:middle line:84%
So he changed the environment of
each one of those Petri dishes,

00:45:15.060 --> 00:45:21.810 align:middle line:84%
and those identical cells
in dish A made skin cells,

00:45:21.810 --> 00:45:28.930 align:middle line:84%
in dish B made bone cells,
and in dish C made fat cells.

00:45:28.930 --> 00:45:33.280 align:middle line:84%
So here, we have
an identical cell,

00:45:33.280 --> 00:45:36.780 align:middle line:84%
and each cell has a
DNA molecule in it.

00:45:36.780 --> 00:45:40.620 align:middle line:84%
And yet, by changing
the environment,

00:45:40.620 --> 00:45:44.050 align:middle line:84%
the cell changed to
a different form.

00:45:44.050 --> 00:45:46.860 align:middle line:84%
So in fact, what that
experiment showed

00:45:46.860 --> 00:45:51.630 align:middle line:84%
was that you may inherit
genes from your parents

00:45:51.630 --> 00:45:54.930 align:middle line:84%
to have a likelihood
of developing

00:45:54.930 --> 00:45:57.330 align:middle line:90%
if you do one thing--

00:45:57.330 --> 00:46:01.200 align:middle line:90%
continue the same environment.

00:46:01.200 --> 00:46:04.380 align:middle line:84%
We eat the same as
our parents did.

00:46:04.380 --> 00:46:06.870 align:middle line:84%
We create the same
stresses in our lives.

00:46:06.870 --> 00:46:09.330 align:middle line:90%
We tend to become replicas.

00:46:09.330 --> 00:46:11.730 align:middle line:84%
What happens when you
create the same environment,

00:46:11.730 --> 00:46:13.520 align:middle line:90%
and you have the same genes?

00:46:13.520 --> 00:46:15.120 align:middle line:90%
You have the same outcome.

00:46:15.120 --> 00:46:19.270 align:middle line:90%
But we do have now the choice.

00:46:19.270 --> 00:46:22.410 align:middle line:84%
It is not just purely
genetics and fate.

00:46:22.410 --> 00:46:25.435 align:middle line:84%
We know that if we
change the environment--

00:46:25.435 --> 00:46:27.810 align:middle line:84%
and the biggest environment
that our cells are sitting in

00:46:27.810 --> 00:46:30.720 align:middle line:90%
is the internal environment--

00:46:30.720 --> 00:46:32.880 align:middle line:84%
when we change that
environment, we

00:46:32.880 --> 00:46:36.910 align:middle line:84%
can then start to expect
a different outcome.

00:46:36.910 --> 00:46:39.810 align:middle line:84%
So perhaps if we take
that knowledge that we do

00:46:39.810 --> 00:46:43.980 align:middle line:84%
have some control, that
we can take responsibility

00:46:43.980 --> 00:46:46.980 align:middle line:84%
for our health,
perhaps we can start

00:46:46.980 --> 00:46:54.660 align:middle line:84%
looking at what we do when
we well intentionally pour

00:46:54.660 --> 00:46:57.720 align:middle line:84%
millions of dollars into
cancer research that

00:46:57.720 --> 00:47:01.200 align:middle line:84%
tends to focus on
finding a cure,

00:47:01.200 --> 00:47:03.270 align:middle line:84%
when perhaps we
could spend a little

00:47:03.270 --> 00:47:07.280 align:middle line:84%
more attention on the
