that structure around the whole
food so that you can absorb

00:58:16.420 --> 00:58:19.750 align:middle line:84%
and properly assimilate
that lycopene.

00:58:19.750 --> 00:58:23.470 align:middle line:84%
So to simplify the
question, if nature

00:58:23.470 --> 00:58:29.530 align:middle line:84%
has provided it in its raw form,
then that's the amount we need.

00:58:29.530 --> 00:58:32.950 align:middle line:84%
>> 14 years ago, I was
diagnosed with cancer,

00:58:32.950 --> 00:58:35.890 align:middle line:84%
and I was told I had
six months to live.

00:58:35.890 --> 00:58:39.850 align:middle line:84%
Now, I wanted a refund
on that really seriously.

00:58:39.850 --> 00:58:43.730 align:middle line:84%
At 50 years old, that
just wasn't enough for me.

00:58:43.730 --> 00:58:45.730 align:middle line:84%
Plus, I also had
a little grandson,

00:58:45.730 --> 00:58:49.760 align:middle line:84%
and I just was not
going to accept that.

00:58:49.760 --> 00:58:55.060 align:middle line:84%
So I started looking into
all of the other options that

00:58:55.060 --> 00:58:56.290 align:middle line:90%
were available.

00:58:56.290 --> 00:58:58.600 align:middle line:84%
Even with the
recommended treatment,

00:58:58.600 --> 00:59:00.640 align:middle line:84%
it wasn't going to make
any difference, apart

00:59:00.640 --> 00:59:03.700 align:middle line:84%
from maybe an extra six
months of being ill.

00:59:03.700 --> 00:59:08.560 align:middle line:84%
So we decided to just
to look into other ways

00:59:08.560 --> 00:59:13.040 align:middle line:84%
that we could make a
difference to that prognosis.

00:59:13.040 --> 00:59:14.470 align:middle line:90%
And what do you know?

00:59:14.470 --> 00:59:17.950 align:middle line:84%
We didn't come up
with something.

00:59:17.950 --> 00:59:22.360 align:middle line:84%
We decided to change
what we were eating,

00:59:22.360 --> 00:59:24.310 align:middle line:84%
think more consciously
about every choice

00:59:24.310 --> 00:59:25.750 align:middle line:90%
that we make in life.

00:59:25.750 --> 00:59:29.170 align:middle line:84%
Within that six months,
it made the difference,

00:59:29.170 --> 00:59:31.360 align:middle line:90%
and I no longer had cancer.

00:59:31.360 --> 00:59:38.440 align:middle line:84%
So that was also the beginning
of our being 100% raw vegan,

00:59:38.440 --> 00:59:41.620 align:middle line:84%
which really was to
do with being 100%

00:59:41.620 --> 00:59:45.340 align:middle line:84%
or having 100%
nutrient-laden food

00:59:45.340 --> 00:59:48.520 align:middle line:84%
so that I would get 100%
the best I could possibly

00:59:48.520 --> 00:59:50.200 align:middle line:90%
get for my body.

00:59:50.200 --> 00:59:54.970 align:middle line:84%
In doing so, not only
did it cure the cancer,

00:59:54.970 --> 00:59:59.810 align:middle line:84%
but also, it made us more
healthy overall physically,

00:59:59.810 --> 01:00:02.470 align:middle line:90%
mentally, and spiritually--

01:00:02.470 --> 01:00:06.180 align:middle line:84%
basically getting
younger every day.

01:00:06.180 --> 01:00:10.120 align:middle line:84%
We decided that we would maybe
do something that would really

01:00:10.120 --> 01:00:13.180 align:middle line:84%
catch the attention of
everybody worldwide,

01:00:13.180 --> 01:00:16.090 align:middle line:84%
and that was to run
around Australia--

01:00:16.090 --> 01:00:19.900 align:middle line:84%
run a marathon a day, every
day, for a whole year.

01:00:19.900 --> 01:00:22.270 align:middle line:84%
And whenever we talked
to anybody about it,

01:00:22.270 --> 01:00:23.770 align:middle line:84%
they said, well,
you know, you won't

01:00:23.770 --> 01:00:28.580 align:middle line:84%
be able to maintain it on
just fruit and vegetables.

01:00:28.580 --> 01:00:31.570 align:middle line:84%
So the point that we
were trying to make

01:00:31.570 --> 01:00:35.440 align:middle line:84%
was that, yes, you can,
that the nutrition that you

01:00:35.440 --> 01:00:41.920 align:middle line:84%
can get from pure, raw,
whole food that's plant-based

01:00:41.920 --> 01:00:44.140 align:middle line:90%
is 100% the best you can get.

01:00:44.140 --> 01:00:46.720 align:middle line:84%
So why would you choose to
have anything less than 100%

01:00:46.720 --> 01:00:48.760 align:middle line:90%
for yourself, for your health?

01:00:48.760 --> 01:00:50.620 align:middle line:84%
And then when you
realize how that's all

01:00:50.620 --> 01:00:52.630 align:middle line:84%
connected to the
health of all living

01:00:52.630 --> 01:00:55.260 align:middle line:84%
beings and the whole
planet, it's a no-brainer.

01:00:55.260 --> 01:00:56.060 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

01:00:56.060 --> 01:00:59.560 align:middle line:84%
>> So we just wanted to show
how simple and easy it is

01:00:59.560 --> 01:01:02.860 align:middle line:84%
to actually achieve
something beyond imagination.

01:01:02.860 --> 01:01:04.180 align:middle line:90%
So that's what we did.

01:01:04.180 --> 01:01:08.440 align:middle line:84%
In 2013, we ran
a marathon a day,

01:01:08.440 --> 01:01:10.000 align:middle line:90%
every day, around Australia.

01:01:10.000 --> 01:01:12.250 align:middle line:84%
We had a crew with
us, two people that

01:01:12.250 --> 01:01:14.290 align:middle line:90%
were driving our two vehicles.

01:01:14.290 --> 01:01:17.050 align:middle line:84%
And every day that we
finished one marathon,

01:01:17.050 --> 01:01:20.890 align:middle line:84%
we would stop right there
and start the marathon again

01:01:20.890 --> 01:01:23.620 align:middle line:84%
the following day so that
it was a continuous run

01:01:23.620 --> 01:01:28.870 align:middle line:84%
all the way for
15,782 kilometers--

01:01:28.870 --> 01:01:30.730 align:middle line:90%
around about 10,000 miles.

01:01:30.730 --> 01:01:33.400 align:middle line:84%
We also included
Tasmania because that

01:01:33.400 --> 01:01:35.930 align:middle line:90%
is part of Australia.

01:01:35.930 --> 01:01:39.010 align:middle line:84%
>> So people would ask us
often, what do you eat?

01:01:39.010 --> 01:01:42.220 align:middle line:84%
I mean, how did you fuel
yourself for this run?

01:01:42.220 --> 01:01:45.010 align:middle line:84%
And as we said before,
the year before,

01:01:45.010 --> 01:01:46.760 align:middle line:84%
we were sort of
practicing how much

01:01:46.760 --> 01:01:49.180 align:middle line:90%
that we could actually eat.

01:01:49.180 --> 01:01:51.190 align:middle line:84%
So during the run,
a typical day would

01:01:51.190 --> 01:01:53.740 align:middle line:84%
be we get up in the
morning around 4:00,

01:01:53.740 --> 01:01:56.890 align:middle line:84%
make ourselves a
large smoothie--

01:01:56.890 --> 01:01:59.890 align:middle line:84%
lots of bananas,
grapefruit, any fruit

01:01:59.890 --> 01:02:02.590 align:middle line:84%
that was sort of hanging
around the caravan.

01:02:02.590 --> 01:02:06.280 align:middle line:84%
And we would drink that
slowly between 4:00 and 5:00

01:02:06.280 --> 01:02:09.670 align:middle line:84%
in the morning because that
was to be the first part

01:02:09.670 --> 01:02:11.860 align:middle line:90%
of our fuel for the day.

01:02:11.860 --> 01:02:14.050 align:middle line:84%
Then, we would take off
about 5:00 in the morning.

01:02:14.050 --> 01:02:16.540 align:middle line:84%
It was usually just
getting light, or perhaps

01:02:16.540 --> 01:02:20.350 align:middle line:84%
the first half an hour,
we'd be running in the dark.

01:02:20.350 --> 01:02:24.370 align:middle line:84%
Eventually, our crew would
actually catch up to us,

01:02:24.370 --> 01:02:26.730 align:middle line:84%
and we'd stop and
have a small smack.

01:02:26.730 --> 01:02:28.240 align:middle line:84%
And usually, our
small snack would

01:02:28.240 --> 01:02:31.700 align:middle line:84%
be anything from 5
to 10 bananas each,

01:02:31.700 --> 01:02:35.768 align:middle line:84%
just to keep us going until
the next smoothie break.

01:02:35.768 --> 01:02:37.810 align:middle line:84%
The next smoothie break
was usually about halfway

01:02:37.810 --> 01:02:39.200 align:middle line:90%
through the run.

01:02:39.200 --> 01:02:44.050 align:middle line:84%
So at about 20k, 13 miles
into the run, we would stop,

01:02:44.050 --> 01:02:47.690 align:middle line:84%
and the crew would have made
us another large smoothie.

01:02:47.690 --> 01:02:49.690 align:middle line:84%
Smoothies are great because
we could digest them

01:02:49.690 --> 01:02:52.510 align:middle line:84%
as we were running, and
they didn't take long

01:02:52.510 --> 01:02:54.460 align:middle line:90%
to sort of chug down.

01:02:54.460 --> 01:02:57.220 align:middle line:84%
And then, at the end
of the day, the crew

01:02:57.220 --> 01:02:58.970 align:middle line:84%
would have made
us a large salad.

01:02:58.970 --> 01:03:01.510 align:middle line:84%
So we'd have a
big bowl of salad,

01:03:01.510 --> 01:03:03.340 align:middle line:84%
usually with a couple
of avocados each

01:03:03.340 --> 01:03:09.040 align:middle line:84%
because that time of the day, we
were often sort of craving fat.

01:03:09.040 --> 01:03:10.610 align:middle line:84%
So it seemed like
a logical thing.

01:03:10.610 --> 01:03:13.630 align:middle line:84%
If we had some, we'd have
a couple of avocados, maybe

01:03:13.630 --> 01:03:17.080 align:middle line:90%
some olives, a big salad.

01:03:17.080 --> 01:03:21.000 align:middle line:84%
But also, just before that, we
would make a big veggie juice--

01:03:21.000 --> 01:03:25.190 align:middle line:84%
some beetroot, carrots,
apples, ginger, turmeric,

01:03:25.190 --> 01:03:25.990 align:middle line:90%
that sort of thing.

01:03:25.990 --> 01:03:26.790 align:middle line:90%
>> And greens.

01:03:26.790 --> 01:03:29.780 align:middle line:84%
>> And we had that as soon as we
stopped at the end of the day.

01:03:29.780 --> 01:03:32.540 align:middle line:90%
Then the salad and the avocados.

01:03:32.540 --> 01:03:34.790 align:middle line:84%
And by then, it was
time to go to bed,

01:03:34.790 --> 01:03:37.323 align:middle line:84%
try and get eight hours of
sleep before the next morning.

01:03:37.323 --> 01:03:40.070 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah. so it was--

01:03:40.070 --> 01:03:46.910 align:middle line:84%
it was sleep, eat, and run;
sleep, eat, and run 366 times.

01:03:46.910 --> 01:03:47.930 align:middle line:90%
Pretty much.

01:03:47.930 --> 01:03:52.520 align:middle line:84%
We did not get injured
from running the whole run.

01:03:52.520 --> 01:03:58.710 align:middle line:84%
So 366 consecutive marathons, we
had no running injuries at all.

01:03:58.710 --> 01:04:01.520 align:middle line:84%
We had no blisters,
and that's because we

01:04:01.520 --> 01:04:02.960 align:middle line:90%
were wearing barefoot shoes.

01:04:02.960 --> 01:04:05.240 align:middle line:84%
So we were-- the
shoes themselves,

01:04:05.240 --> 01:04:07.610 align:middle line:84%
it's like being
barefoot, really.

01:04:07.610 --> 01:04:09.710 align:middle line:84%
But the other thing
about them is that they

01:04:09.710 --> 01:04:11.090 align:middle line:90%
assimilate barefoot running.

01:04:11.090 --> 01:04:14.240 align:middle line:84%
So you run correctly
and naturally,

01:04:14.240 --> 01:04:16.010 align:middle line:90%
so we had no injuries from that.

01:04:16.010 --> 01:04:18.980 align:middle line:84%
We did get injured a couple
of times from falling.

01:04:18.980 --> 01:04:22.160 align:middle line:84%
Both of us had cracked
ribs for different falls.

01:04:22.160 --> 01:04:29.840 align:middle line:84%
And also, our elbows and
knees took a bit of a whack

01:04:29.840 --> 01:04:31.670 align:middle line:90%
there when we fell.

01:04:31.670 --> 01:04:33.320 align:middle line:90%
But we continued.

01:04:33.320 --> 01:04:36.800 align:middle line:84%
So we were able to
actually recover,

01:04:36.800 --> 01:04:40.820 align:middle line:84%
not only from the running,
but from the injury as we ran.

01:04:40.820 --> 01:04:42.800 align:middle line:90%
So we were healing as we ran.

01:04:42.800 --> 01:04:44.960 align:middle line:84%
And I think that
that's really important

01:04:44.960 --> 01:04:48.500 align:middle line:84%
to make a point because
without the type of nutrients

01:04:48.500 --> 01:04:51.475 align:middle line:84%
that we were getting, that
would not have been possible.

01:04:51.475 --> 01:04:52.850 align:middle line:84%
I mean, just doing
the running, I

01:04:52.850 --> 01:04:54.433 align:middle line:84%
don't think, would
have been possible,

01:04:54.433 --> 01:04:57.680 align:middle line:84%
either-- not to
continue for that long.

01:04:57.680 --> 01:05:01.150 align:middle line:84%
>> During the run, we
didn't take any supplements.

01:05:01.150 --> 01:05:01.950 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

01:05:01.950 --> 01:05:05.240 align:middle line:84%
>> We didn't take
any painkillers.

01:05:05.240 --> 01:05:07.130 align:middle line:84%
We just had, like
you can see here,

01:05:07.130 --> 01:05:09.340 align:middle line:90%
just raw fruit and vegetables.

01:05:09.340 --> 01:05:10.160 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

01:05:10.160 --> 01:05:13.670 align:middle line:84%
Within that six months,
there was already

01:05:13.670 --> 01:05:17.180 align:middle line:84%
a huge amount of people
sitting up and taking notice

01:05:17.180 --> 01:05:18.860 align:middle line:90%
and wanting to know.

01:05:18.860 --> 01:05:21.290 align:middle line:84%
The question wasn't where do
you get your protein anymore.

01:05:21.290 --> 01:05:23.340 align:middle line:90%
It was wow, this is amazing.

01:05:23.340 --> 01:05:26.060 align:middle line:84%
You're doing this on raw
fruits and vegetables.

01:05:26.060 --> 01:05:30.620 align:middle line:84%
But our answer to that was,
that's actually not amazing.

01:05:30.620 --> 01:05:32.950 align:middle line:90%
That's how it should be.

01:05:32.950 --> 01:05:34.940 align:middle line:84%
What would be amazing
would be if we

01:05:34.940 --> 01:05:36.680 align:middle line:90%
were doing it on anything else.

01:05:36.680 --> 01:05:39.380 align:middle line:84%
So it was-- it
was something that

01:05:39.380 --> 01:05:45.470 align:middle line:84%
was really starting to capture
the interest with everybody.

01:05:45.470 --> 01:05:49.790 align:middle line:84%
By the time we finished, we had
a huge amount of people there

01:05:49.790 --> 01:05:53.780 align:middle line:84%
and media there to welcome
us in because not only had we

01:05:53.780 --> 01:05:57.860 align:middle line:84%
achieved something really
amazing for most people,

01:05:57.860 --> 01:06:00.470 align:middle line:84%
but we had also
set a world record.

01:06:00.470 --> 01:06:04.970 align:middle line:84%
The message that was
conveyed in the run,

01:06:04.970 --> 01:06:09.560 align:middle line:84%
I think, was more important
than the run itself.

01:06:09.560 --> 01:06:12.710 align:middle line:84%
What the run did was bring
that message to the fore,

01:06:12.710 --> 01:06:15.770 align:middle line:84%
and that message
is that we all need

01:06:15.770 --> 01:06:19.500 align:middle line:84%
to look at making more
conscious lifestyle choices.

01:06:19.500 --> 01:06:22.010 align:middle line:84%
So every choice in our
life is a conscious one.

01:06:22.010 --> 01:06:24.260 align:middle line:84%
We're thinking
consciously about what

01:06:24.260 --> 01:06:28.520 align:middle line:90%
the response to that choice is.

01:06:28.520 --> 01:06:32.190 align:middle line:84%
And that's not just with food,
but with everything we do.

01:06:32.190 --> 01:06:33.830 align:middle line:84%
And if everybody
in the world was

01:06:33.830 --> 01:06:37.010 align:middle line:84%
to be thinking more consciously
about their choices,

01:06:37.010 --> 01:06:40.310 align:middle line:84%
what an amazing
change there would be.

01:06:40.310 --> 01:06:42.080 align:middle line:84%
So a lot of people
ask us if we're

01:06:42.080 --> 01:06:46.430 align:middle line:84%
happy with what we achieved,
and the world record really

01:06:46.430 --> 01:06:48.740 align:middle line:90%
has nothing to do with us--

01:06:48.740 --> 01:06:50.120 align:middle line:90%
even the run.

01:06:50.120 --> 01:06:53.720 align:middle line:84%
What we achieved was bringing
this really positive message

01:06:53.720 --> 01:06:56.780 align:middle line:84%
to the world, and
we're continuing

01:06:56.780 --> 01:06:59.250 align:middle line:84%
to do that in any
way we possibly can.

01:06:59.250 --> 01:07:02.450 align:middle line:84%
And I think that is a
much greater achievement.

01:07:02.450 --> 01:07:09.200 align:middle line:84%
The run itself-- yes, at
the ages of 64 for me and 68

01:07:09.200 --> 01:07:10.820 align:middle line:90%
at the time for Alan--

01:07:10.820 --> 01:07:16.130 align:middle line:84%
I think that pretty much says
a huge amount that you're never

01:07:16.130 --> 01:07:19.130 align:middle line:84%
too old to make
changes that will make

01:07:19.130 --> 01:07:21.050 align:middle line:90%
a difference to your health.

01:07:21.050 --> 01:07:23.620 align:middle line:90%
And for myself, you never--

01:07:23.620 --> 01:07:28.970 align:middle line:84%
you know, making those
changes for a difference

01:07:28.970 --> 01:07:31.940 align:middle line:84%
to your health, if you
have health issues,

01:07:31.940 --> 01:07:35.180 align:middle line:90%
is huge as well, clearly.

01:07:35.180 --> 01:07:39.170 align:middle line:84%
So 100% raw vegan
plant-based diet,

01:07:39.170 --> 01:07:45.783 align:middle line:84%
which we've been on for 14 years
now just keeps getting better.

01:07:45.783 --> 01:07:48.200 align:middle line:84%
It's not that it makes a huge
difference in the beginning.

01:07:48.200 --> 01:07:50.930 align:middle line:84%
It certainly does,
but it continues

01:07:50.930 --> 01:07:52.730 align:middle line:90%
to make that difference.

01:07:52.730 --> 01:07:56.160 align:middle line:84%
Every day, there's
something different for us.

01:07:56.160 --> 01:07:57.410 align:middle line:90%
Every day, we think--

01:07:57.410 --> 01:08:01.130 align:middle line:84%
we get up in the morning, we
go for our early morning run,

01:08:01.130 --> 01:08:03.170 align:middle line:84%
and we think, what's
today going to bring?

01:08:03.170 --> 01:08:07.310 align:middle line:84%
It's exciting because we
know that whatever it is,

01:08:07.310 --> 01:08:10.910 align:middle line:84%
we're going to enjoy it, and
we're capable of anything.

01:08:10.910 --> 01:08:13.250 align:middle line:84%
That's something
that a lot of people

01:08:13.250 --> 01:08:16.050 align:middle line:84%
probably don't understand
because they haven't been there

01:08:16.050 --> 01:08:16.850 align:middle line:90%
yet.

01:08:16.850 --> 01:08:22.189 align:middle line:84%
But when you're living a
fully conscious lifestyle,

01:08:22.189 --> 01:08:24.109 align:middle line:90%
anything's possible.

01:08:24.109 --> 01:08:27.500 align:middle line:84%
Anything at all that you think
of that you might want to do,

01:08:27.500 --> 01:08:31.899 align:middle line:84%
that you might want to
experience, it's possible.

01:08:31.899 --> 01:08:35.620 align:middle line:84%
But not only that, what's
possible beyond what

01:08:35.620 --> 01:08:36.939 align:middle line:90%
we don't know yet?

01:08:36.939 --> 01:08:39.300 align:middle line:90%
And that's really important.

01:08:39.300 --> 01:08:40.660 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

01:08:40.660 --> 01:08:45.490 align:middle line:84%
I think a point that we must
make here, too, is so simple.

01:08:45.490 --> 01:08:49.300 align:middle line:84%
When we first went raw,
we were into making things

01:08:49.300 --> 01:08:52.600 align:middle line:84%
like raw pizzas and
raw lasagna, but after

01:08:52.600 --> 01:08:56.979 align:middle line:84%
14 years of being raw, now,
we just eat a banana or make

01:08:56.979 --> 01:08:58.630 align:middle line:90%
a smoothie.

01:08:58.630 --> 01:09:03.399 align:middle line:84%
We don't go to any trouble,
and it's so simple.

01:09:03.399 --> 01:09:06.890 align:middle line:84%
We hear people say, ah, it's so
hard to be on a raw food diet,

01:09:06.890 --> 01:09:08.590 align:middle line:90%
but it's just the opposite.

01:09:08.590 --> 01:09:12.609 align:middle line:84%
The longer you do it,
the easier it gets.

01:09:12.609 --> 01:09:15.545 align:middle line:84%
>> People with diabetes
are often concerned,

01:09:15.545 --> 01:09:17.170 align:middle line:84%
and they're even told
by their doctors,

01:09:17.170 --> 01:09:19.250 align:middle line:84%
don't eat fruit because
fruit has sugar in it,

01:09:19.250 --> 01:09:21.083 align:middle line:84%
and it's going to raise
your blood sugar up,

01:09:21.083 --> 01:09:22.510 align:middle line:90%
make your diabetes worse.

01:09:22.510 --> 01:09:24.460 align:middle line:90%
But wait a minute.

01:09:24.460 --> 01:09:28.660 align:middle line:84%
Fruit sugars generally are
metabolized very quickly.

01:09:28.660 --> 01:09:31.510 align:middle line:84%
Healthy people do not walk
around high blood sugars

01:09:31.510 --> 01:09:33.250 align:middle line:84%
even though they
have some watermelon

01:09:33.250 --> 01:09:35.020 align:middle line:90%
or cantaloupe for breakfast.

01:09:35.020 --> 01:09:36.930 align:middle line:84%
What's the problem with
the diabetic person?

01:09:36.930 --> 01:09:40.060 align:middle line:84%
Is it really their
inability to handle sugars?

01:09:40.060 --> 01:09:43.010 align:middle line:84%
Actually, the sugars
aren't the problem at all.

01:09:43.010 --> 01:09:45.460 align:middle line:84%
It's the saturated fats
that they've been eating

01:09:45.460 --> 01:09:48.729 align:middle line:84%
and the animal products
and the junky oils

01:09:48.729 --> 01:09:50.529 align:middle line:90%
that they've been eating.

01:09:50.529 --> 01:09:53.680 align:middle line:84%
These fats get into
the muscle cells,

01:09:53.680 --> 01:09:57.700 align:middle line:84%
and they block the
receptors for insulin.

01:09:57.700 --> 01:09:59.950 align:middle line:84%
So insulin, which
is necessary to move

01:09:59.950 --> 01:10:03.490 align:middle line:84%
that sugar from the bloodstream
into the muscle cells where

01:10:03.490 --> 01:10:04.540 align:middle line:90%
it can be burned--

01:10:04.540 --> 01:10:08.710 align:middle line:84%
that insulin is blocked from
doing its essential action

01:10:08.710 --> 01:10:12.130 align:middle line:84%
because the insulin receptors
are all clogged up with fat.

01:10:12.130 --> 01:10:14.860 align:middle line:84%
And it's the fat in the diet
that's causing the insulin

01:10:14.860 --> 01:10:18.190 align:middle line:84%
resistance, and that
makes the sugar pile up

01:10:18.190 --> 01:10:19.760 align:middle line:90%
in the bloodstream.

01:10:19.760 --> 01:10:22.825 align:middle line:84%
So the focus should not
be on the fruit sugar.

01:10:22.825 --> 01:10:26.130 align:middle line:84%
The problem is the fat
that person's been eating,

01:10:26.130 --> 01:10:29.890 align:middle line:84%
and we're talking about
saturated animal fats here.

01:10:29.890 --> 01:10:33.250 align:middle line:84%
The fats found in whole
vegetable, whole plant

01:10:33.250 --> 01:10:34.090 align:middle line:90%
products--

01:10:34.090 --> 01:10:36.730 align:middle line:84%
the ellagic acid in
avocados and nuts--

01:10:36.730 --> 01:10:40.840 align:middle line:84%
really don't have this insulin
receptor blocking effect.

01:10:40.840 --> 01:10:43.130 align:middle line:84%
But it's the stearic
acid, palmitic acid

01:10:43.130 --> 01:10:45.460 align:middle line:84%
that's in animal fat,
gets into the muscle

01:10:45.460 --> 01:10:47.560 align:middle line:84%
cells, blocks the
insulin receptors

01:10:47.560 --> 01:10:49.510 align:middle line:90%
so insulin can't work.

01:10:49.510 --> 01:10:52.750 align:middle line:84%
So the fruit gets blamed
when the real problem

01:10:52.750 --> 01:10:55.030 align:middle line:84%
is the saturated fats
from the animal products

01:10:55.030 --> 01:10:57.520 align:middle line:84%
that's clogging up
the insulin receptors.

01:10:57.520 --> 01:11:01.180 align:middle line:84%
So as we predictably see
Type-2 diabetes go away

01:11:01.180 --> 01:11:03.460 align:middle line:84%
as people adopt a whole
food, plant-based diet,

01:11:03.460 --> 01:11:05.260 align:middle line:90%
take a walk every day.

01:11:05.260 --> 01:11:09.490 align:middle line:84%
They'll burn that fat that's in
their muscle cells for energy,

01:11:09.490 --> 01:11:11.740 align:middle line:84%
and their insulin
receptors open up.

01:11:11.740 --> 01:11:14.380 align:middle line:84%
And the insulin they
make starts working fine.

01:11:14.380 --> 01:11:16.780 align:middle line:84%
And they find they can then
eat the apple or the banana

01:11:16.780 --> 01:11:19.030 align:middle line:84%
and the cantaloupe, and
their blood sugar does not

01:11:19.030 --> 01:11:20.488 align:middle line:84%
go to dangerous
levels, and they're

01:11:20.488 --> 01:11:22.460 align:middle line:90%
able to eat fruit just fine.

01:11:22.460 --> 01:11:24.880 align:middle line:84%
So again, the
fruit and the sugar

01:11:24.880 --> 01:11:27.460 align:middle line:84%
elevations that come from it
in the diabetic person-- that's

01:11:27.460 --> 01:11:29.020 align:middle line:90%
the tail of the dog.

01:11:29.020 --> 01:11:31.090 align:middle line:84%
You've got to go up to
the business end there.

01:11:31.090 --> 01:11:33.340 align:middle line:84%
It's the fats that they're
eating that are clogging up

01:11:33.340 --> 01:11:35.710 align:middle line:84%
their insulin receptors that's
really causing the high blood

01:11:35.710 --> 01:11:36.510 align:middle line:90%
sugars.

01:11:36.510 --> 01:11:39.710 align:middle line:84%
So fruits are wonderful
parts of the human diet,

01:11:39.710 --> 01:11:41.530 align:middle line:84%
and they add the
sweetness in life.

01:11:41.530 --> 01:11:44.230 align:middle line:84%
And so I'm a big fan of
ample amounts of fruit.

01:11:44.230 --> 01:11:47.500 align:middle line:84%
But keep your instant receptors
open from a plant-based diet,

01:11:47.500 --> 01:11:49.660 align:middle line:84%
and you'll be able to have
all the fruit you want

01:11:49.660 --> 01:11:52.077 align:middle line:84%
without worrying about what
it's doing to your blood sugar

01:11:52.077 --> 01:11:53.200 align:middle line:90%
levels.

01:11:53.200 --> 01:11:58.730 align:middle line:84%
>> Probably the fundamental
key to healing is for us all

01:11:58.730 --> 01:12:01.430 align:middle line:84%
to take responsibility
for our own health.

01:12:01.430 --> 01:12:05.510 align:middle line:84%
