And two weeks ago, I gave
a speech here in Melbourne

01:21:19.930 --> 01:21:23.200 align:middle line:84%
with Dr. Peter Doherty,
who won Australia's Nobel

01:21:23.200 --> 01:21:25.240 align:middle line:90%
Prize in medicine.

01:21:25.240 --> 01:21:28.840 align:middle line:84%
And I presented these gentlemen
with all the same numbers

01:21:28.840 --> 01:21:33.730 align:middle line:84%
and algorithms, and no arguments
from any of these Nobel

01:21:33.730 --> 01:21:36.880 align:middle line:84%
laureates, but
plenty of arguments

01:21:36.880 --> 01:21:40.390 align:middle line:84%
from the meat and dairy
lobby and the politicians who

01:21:40.390 --> 01:21:45.370 align:middle line:84%
seem to toe the line whenever
the lobby group calls.

01:21:45.370 --> 01:21:47.710 align:middle line:90%
So Upton Sinclair was right.

01:21:47.710 --> 01:21:50.800 align:middle line:84%
It isn't possible to get a
man to understand something

01:21:50.800 --> 01:21:53.570 align:middle line:84%
when his salary depends on
him not understanding it.

01:21:53.570 --> 01:21:56.940 align:middle line:90%


01:21:56.940 --> 01:22:00.870 align:middle line:84%
Admiral [INAUDIBLE],, the chief
of US warfighting requirements,

01:22:00.870 --> 01:22:05.460 align:middle line:84%
said, we have learned that
nations will raid and invade

01:22:05.460 --> 01:22:07.680 align:middle line:90%
long before they starve.

01:22:07.680 --> 01:22:10.740 align:middle line:84%
And we freak out in
Australia when 1,000 refugees

01:22:10.740 --> 01:22:12.285 align:middle line:90%
arrive on our shores.

01:22:12.285 --> 01:22:15.060 align:middle line:84%
Now, just imagine
greenhouse gas emissions

01:22:15.060 --> 01:22:18.480 align:middle line:84%
hitting 500 parts per million
or a three degree temperature

01:22:18.480 --> 01:22:23.700 align:middle line:84%
rise, creating 100
million eco-refugees.

01:22:23.700 --> 01:22:28.750 align:middle line:84%
This calamity will reshape the
geopolitical landscape forever.

01:22:28.750 --> 01:22:32.080 align:middle line:90%
We are facing the perfect storm.

01:22:32.080 --> 01:22:34.170 align:middle line:84%
If any other nation
were to develop weapons

01:22:34.170 --> 01:22:36.480 align:middle line:84%
that could wreak such
havoc on the planet,

01:22:36.480 --> 01:22:39.150 align:middle line:84%
we would launch a
pre-emptive military strike

01:22:39.150 --> 01:22:41.970 align:middle line:84%
and bomb it back
into the Bronze Age.

01:22:41.970 --> 01:22:46.210 align:middle line:84%
But we can't because it
is not a rogue state.

01:22:46.210 --> 01:22:48.190 align:middle line:90%
It's an industry.

01:22:48.190 --> 01:22:51.070 align:middle line:84%
The good news is, we
don't have to bomb it.

01:22:51.070 --> 01:22:53.890 align:middle line:90%
We can just stop buying it.

01:22:53.890 --> 01:22:56.380 align:middle line:90%
So George Bush was wrong.

01:22:56.380 --> 01:22:59.620 align:middle line:84%
The Axis of Evil does not
run through Iraq, Iran,

01:22:59.620 --> 01:23:01.120 align:middle line:90%
or North Korea.

01:23:01.120 --> 01:23:03.700 align:middle line:84%
It runs through
our dining tables.

01:23:03.700 --> 01:23:07.780 align:middle line:84%
Weapons of mass destruction
are our knives and forks,

01:23:07.780 --> 01:23:10.600 align:middle line:84%
and farmers are the ones
with the most to gain.

01:23:10.600 --> 01:23:12.280 align:middle line:90%
Farming wouldn't end.

01:23:12.280 --> 01:23:16.210 align:middle line:84%
It would boom-- only the
product line would change.

01:23:16.210 --> 01:23:19.240 align:middle line:84%
I often say that veganism
is the Swiss army

01:23:19.240 --> 01:23:22.630 align:middle line:84%
knife of an ethical
and authentic future.

01:23:22.630 --> 01:23:26.140 align:middle line:84%
One instrument solves
all our ethical,

01:23:26.140 --> 01:23:30.490 align:middle line:84%
our financial, environmental,
water, and human health

01:23:30.490 --> 01:23:34.990 align:middle line:84%
problems and ends
animal cruelty forever.

01:23:34.990 --> 01:23:37.840 align:middle line:90%
Veganism is the enchanted key.

01:23:37.840 --> 01:23:43.210 align:middle line:84%
It opens locked doors to secret
rooms in your own castle.

01:23:43.210 --> 01:23:46.900 align:middle line:84%
The Stone Age didn't end
because we ran out of stones.

01:23:46.900 --> 01:23:51.490 align:middle line:84%
This meat industry will end
because we run out of excuses.

01:23:51.490 --> 01:23:55.660 align:middle line:84%
Veganism is the engine of
redirected economic growth.

01:23:55.660 --> 01:23:57.520 align:middle line:90%
Governments would love us.

01:23:57.520 --> 01:24:00.190 align:middle line:84%
New industries would
emerge and flourish.

01:24:00.190 --> 01:24:02.680 align:middle line:84%
Health insurance
premiums would plummet.

01:24:02.680 --> 01:24:05.470 align:middle line:84%
Hospital waiting
lists would disappear.

01:24:05.470 --> 01:24:08.980 align:middle line:84%
Veganism gives us
the peace dividend.

01:24:08.980 --> 01:24:11.680 align:middle line:84%
I addressed the World
Parliament of Religions,

01:24:11.680 --> 01:24:15.850 align:middle line:84%
and I said that the peace
map is drawn on a menu.

01:24:15.850 --> 01:24:18.820 align:middle line:84%
Peace is not just
the absence of war.

01:24:18.820 --> 01:24:21.700 align:middle line:90%
It is the presence of justice.

01:24:21.700 --> 01:24:26.350 align:middle line:84%
Justice must be blind to
race, color, religion,

01:24:26.350 --> 01:24:28.360 align:middle line:90%
and to species.

01:24:28.360 --> 01:24:33.160 align:middle line:84%
If it is not blind, it will
be used as a weapon of terror,

01:24:33.160 --> 01:24:36.030 align:middle line:84%
and today, there is
unimaginable terror

01:24:36.030 --> 01:24:40.660 align:middle line:84%
in those ghastly gulags we call
factory farms and vivisection

01:24:40.660 --> 01:24:43.610 align:middle line:90%
laboratories.

01:24:43.610 --> 01:24:48.830 align:middle line:84%
As Lord Acton said, it is a
place where absolute power

01:24:48.830 --> 01:24:51.140 align:middle line:90%
corrupts absolutely.

01:24:51.140 --> 01:24:54.890 align:middle line:84%
So talking about peace
while still killing animals

01:24:54.890 --> 01:24:58.670 align:middle line:84%
is like loving literature
and burning books.

01:24:58.670 --> 01:25:01.850 align:middle line:84%
They are mutually
exclusive ideas.

01:25:01.850 --> 01:25:04.460 align:middle line:84%
They are incompatible
in the same way

01:25:04.460 --> 01:25:09.560 align:middle line:84%
that science is incompatible
with the Flat Earth Society.

01:25:09.560 --> 01:25:11.510 align:middle line:84%
The last sentence of
Scott Fitzgerald's book

01:25:11.510 --> 01:25:14.960 align:middle line:84%
The Great Gatsby
reads, "so we beat on,

01:25:14.960 --> 01:25:18.620 align:middle line:84%
boats against the tide,
drawn back ceaselessly

01:25:18.620 --> 01:25:20.150 align:middle line:90%
into the past."

01:25:20.150 --> 01:25:24.500 align:middle line:84%
I ask you-- are we to live
forever and a sick, smug,

01:25:24.500 --> 01:25:26.600 align:middle line:90%
and cruel past?

01:25:26.600 --> 01:25:30.422 align:middle line:84%
Our animal cousins have survived
millions of years of evolution.

01:25:30.422 --> 01:25:32.630 align:middle line:84%
They've earned the right to
share this planet with us

01:25:32.630 --> 01:25:33.990 align:middle line:90%
in peace.

01:25:33.990 --> 01:25:37.040 align:middle line:84%
And they have
waited long enough.

01:25:37.040 --> 01:25:39.770 align:middle line:84%
Judge White's closing words
in the Bonfire of the Vanities

01:25:39.770 --> 01:25:46.190 align:middle line:84%
were, "the law is humanity's
clumsy attempt at decency."

01:25:46.190 --> 01:25:52.190 align:middle line:84%
So let's join this battle in the
war that decency cannot afford

01:25:52.190 --> 01:25:56.980 align:middle line:84%
to lose because in the end,
only three things matter--

01:25:56.980 --> 01:26:01.060 align:middle line:84%
how deeply you loved,
how gently you lived,

01:26:01.060 --> 01:26:03.070 align:middle line:84%
and how gracefully
you let go of things

01:26:03.070 --> 01:26:05.740 align:middle line:90%
that were not meant for you.

01:26:05.740 --> 01:26:07.540 align:middle line:90%
Meat was not meant for you.

01:26:07.540 --> 01:26:10.330 align:middle line:90%


01:26:10.330 --> 01:26:13.630 align:middle line:84%
>> One evening, I was
pontificating to a friend about

01:26:13.630 --> 01:26:16.360 align:middle line:84%
wanting to be a
truly peaceful man,

01:26:16.360 --> 01:26:19.000 align:middle line:84%
but I was doing it while
polishing off a 16-ounce

01:26:19.000 --> 01:26:21.880 align:middle line:84%
porterhouse steak at
the local steakhouse.

01:26:21.880 --> 01:26:23.980 align:middle line:84%
And he looked at me
and said, Michael, it's

01:26:23.980 --> 01:26:26.050 align:middle line:84%
all well and good,
but if you really

01:26:26.050 --> 01:26:28.090 align:middle line:84%
want to get the violent
side of your life,

01:26:28.090 --> 01:26:31.120 align:middle line:84%
you might start with that
piece of muscle on your plate

01:26:31.120 --> 01:26:33.460 align:middle line:84%
because in fulfilling
your desire

01:26:33.460 --> 01:26:35.440 align:middle line:84%
for that meat in
your mouth, you are

01:26:35.440 --> 01:26:38.320 align:middle line:84%
paying for the
death of that animal

01:26:38.320 --> 01:26:40.780 align:middle line:84%
and for the next
animal on the assembly

01:26:40.780 --> 01:26:42.900 align:middle line:90%
line in the slaughterhouse.

01:26:42.900 --> 01:26:48.340 align:middle line:84%
And as soon as he said that,
a series of rationalizations

01:26:48.340 --> 01:26:50.440 align:middle line:84%
welled up inside of
me-- oh, well, that's

01:26:50.440 --> 01:26:52.930 align:middle line:84%
what they raised them for,
and it's dead already.

01:26:52.930 --> 01:26:53.770 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't matter.

01:26:53.770 --> 01:26:58.270 align:middle line:84%
But as I was about to say this,
that same little voice said,

01:26:58.270 --> 01:27:00.640 align:middle line:90%
you know, he's right.

01:27:00.640 --> 01:27:02.220 align:middle line:90%
He's right.

01:27:02.220 --> 01:27:05.160 align:middle line:84%
I am complicit in
that animal's death

01:27:05.160 --> 01:27:09.270 align:middle line:84%
every time I pull out my wallet
and pay for a meat-based meal.

01:27:09.270 --> 01:27:11.640 align:middle line:84%
And I knew I could no
longer do that if I

01:27:11.640 --> 01:27:14.820 align:middle line:84%
was going to be a man not only
of peace, but of integrity,

01:27:14.820 --> 01:27:16.430 align:middle line:90%
knowing what I knew.

01:27:16.430 --> 01:27:18.870 align:middle line:84%
I had done much my growing
up on my uncle's dairy farm

01:27:18.870 --> 01:27:19.670 align:middle line:90%
in Wisconsin.

01:27:19.670 --> 01:27:24.270 align:middle line:84%
I knew where meat came from,
and I knew the truth of dairy,

01:27:24.270 --> 01:27:27.540 align:middle line:84%
and I knew at that point
I could no longer pay

01:27:27.540 --> 01:27:29.592 align:middle line:90%
for these animal-based products.

01:27:29.592 --> 01:27:31.800 align:middle line:84%
You know, they say, once
you look behind the curtain,

01:27:31.800 --> 01:27:34.560 align:middle line:84%
you can't pretend you don't
know what's behind the curtain.

01:27:34.560 --> 01:27:36.660 align:middle line:84%
And that curtain had
been ripped down for me.

01:27:36.660 --> 01:27:39.405 align:middle line:90%
There was no escaping the truth.

01:27:39.405 --> 01:27:42.315 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:27:42.315 --> 01:27:52.990 align:middle line:90%


01:27:52.990 --> 01:27:56.155 align:middle line:84%
>> These are Scottish Highland
cattle that we rescued.

01:27:56.155 --> 01:27:57.780 align:middle line:84%
Because we're vegan,
we don't eat them,

01:27:57.780 --> 01:28:03.660 align:middle line:84%
and they come from a guy that
made meat pies out of them.

01:28:03.660 --> 01:28:05.220 align:middle line:84%
So we went and
bought these four,

01:28:05.220 --> 01:28:07.200 align:middle line:84%
and they just live
out their life here.

01:28:07.200 --> 01:28:09.360 align:middle line:90%
We use the manure.

01:28:09.360 --> 01:28:11.670 align:middle line:84%
They were not used
to humans at all

01:28:11.670 --> 01:28:15.760 align:middle line:84%
when they came here about
2 and 1/2 years ago,

01:28:15.760 --> 01:28:18.810 align:middle line:84%
and now they're, just with a
little bit of love and care,

01:28:18.810 --> 01:28:20.580 align:middle line:90%
they're completely friendly.

01:28:20.580 --> 01:28:22.200 align:middle line:90%
They come when they're called.

01:28:22.200 --> 01:28:25.230 align:middle line:84%
They're beautiful, gentle
creatures, lovely animals.

01:28:25.230 --> 01:28:28.690 align:middle line:84%
And these are not chemically
treated or anything.

01:28:28.690 --> 01:28:32.400 align:middle line:84%
They're 100% organic,
free roaming.

01:28:32.400 --> 01:28:39.570 align:middle line:84%
We've got Hamish at the
end, Fergus, Dougal here,

01:28:39.570 --> 01:28:41.120 align:middle line:90%
and Angus there.

01:28:41.120 --> 01:28:43.800 align:middle line:90%


01:28:43.800 --> 01:28:47.970 align:middle line:84%
Nature provides it with
an instinct to live.

01:28:47.970 --> 01:28:49.230 align:middle line:90%
It wants to live.

01:28:49.230 --> 01:28:51.540 align:middle line:90%
It wants to protect its young.

01:28:51.540 --> 01:28:53.400 align:middle line:90%
It runs from danger.

01:28:53.400 --> 01:28:57.900 align:middle line:84%
It goes towards comfort and
warmth, and that's what we do,

01:28:57.900 --> 01:29:00.120 align:middle line:84%
and that's what all
living creatures do.

01:29:00.120 --> 01:29:01.650 align:middle line:90%
And yet we take that--

01:29:01.650 --> 01:29:04.340 align:middle line:84%
we take that from them,
and we end their lives

01:29:04.340 --> 01:29:06.840 align:middle line:84%
just because we want to eat
them when we don't even need to.

01:29:06.840 --> 01:29:10.860 align:middle line:84%
Even the United Nations have
said that we have to change.

01:29:10.860 --> 01:29:13.680 align:middle line:84%
The only way the world
is going to survive

01:29:13.680 --> 01:29:16.500 align:middle line:84%
is to eventually become vegan
because we're eating ourselves

01:29:16.500 --> 01:29:17.430 align:middle line:90%
off the planet.

01:29:17.430 --> 01:29:20.374 align:middle line:84%
We can no longer
sustain the way we eat.

01:29:20.374 --> 01:29:23.853 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:29:23.853 --> 01:29:30.820 align:middle line:90%


01:29:30.820 --> 01:29:33.970 align:middle line:84%
>> Raw food helped to
heal my body, but first,

01:29:33.970 --> 01:29:36.850 align:middle line:84%
I had to heal my mind,
because without addressing

01:29:36.850 --> 01:29:40.120 align:middle line:84%
the tendencies of the mind,
it can sabotage your efforts

01:29:40.120 --> 01:29:43.360 align:middle line:84%
towards self-healing, simply
through your unloving belief

01:29:43.360 --> 01:29:44.930 align:middle line:90%
system.

01:29:44.930 --> 01:29:47.600 align:middle line:84%
I feel it's important to
clarify that whilst diet

01:29:47.600 --> 01:29:50.270 align:middle line:84%
was a huge component
of my healing,

01:29:50.270 --> 01:29:53.300 align:middle line:84%
it was part of a
holistic approach.

01:29:53.300 --> 01:29:55.580 align:middle line:84%
One week after my
attempted suicide,

01:29:55.580 --> 01:29:58.400 align:middle line:84%
I went into a personal
development seminar.

01:29:58.400 --> 01:30:00.140 align:middle line:84%
I went into it
prepared to give it

01:30:00.140 --> 01:30:03.260 align:middle line:84%
everything I had because
I knew that whatever

01:30:03.260 --> 01:30:08.490 align:middle line:84%
I was doing or believed was not
working to help shift my life.

01:30:08.490 --> 01:30:11.750 align:middle line:84%
Unfortunately for me,
every time I took a pill

01:30:11.750 --> 01:30:13.760 align:middle line:84%
or came out of the
doctor's office,

01:30:13.760 --> 01:30:15.860 align:middle line:84%
I had the thought
there is something

01:30:15.860 --> 01:30:18.260 align:middle line:90%
seriously wrong with me.

01:30:18.260 --> 01:30:21.590 align:middle line:84%
Life reinforced this
thought over and over again

01:30:21.590 --> 01:30:24.110 align:middle line:90%
because that is what I believed.

01:30:24.110 --> 01:30:28.220 align:middle line:84%
That is what was always
in the back of my mind.

01:30:28.220 --> 01:30:31.910 align:middle line:84%
My identity had become
depression itself,

01:30:31.910 --> 01:30:33.650 align:middle line:84%
and no matter how
hard I tried, it

01:30:33.650 --> 01:30:37.670 align:middle line:84%
was never enough to fix the
person that I believed myself

01:30:37.670 --> 01:30:39.360 align:middle line:90%
to be.

01:30:39.360 --> 01:30:41.550 align:middle line:84%
I was so numbed
by the medication

01:30:41.550 --> 01:30:45.690 align:middle line:84%
that I knew I was capable of
walking in front of a truck

01:30:45.690 --> 01:30:50.440 align:middle line:84%
or slamming the car into a
tree because I felt no fear.

01:30:50.440 --> 01:30:54.480 align:middle line:84%
I became more and more
disconnected, and as irrational

01:30:54.480 --> 01:30:57.870 align:middle line:84%
as it seems now, I
had convinced myself

01:30:57.870 --> 01:31:01.830 align:middle line:84%
that my children and family
would be better off without me.

01:31:01.830 --> 01:31:05.130 align:middle line:84%
And one day, I followed
through with one of my longings

01:31:05.130 --> 01:31:09.420 align:middle line:84%
to go to sleep forever
by taking an overdose.

01:31:09.420 --> 01:31:13.830 align:middle line:84%
I came out of that seminar with
a profoundly different view

01:31:13.830 --> 01:31:17.520 align:middle line:84%
and understanding of
how I perceived life.

01:31:17.520 --> 01:31:21.990 align:middle line:84%
I used that new understanding
as the catalyst for change.

01:31:21.990 --> 01:31:25.980 align:middle line:84%
That weekend, I decided I
was willing to do whatever

01:31:25.980 --> 01:31:32.880 align:middle line:84%
it took to help myself,
and my love for my children

01:31:32.880 --> 01:31:37.800 align:middle line:90%
provided me with the motivation.

01:31:37.800 --> 01:31:40.590 align:middle line:84%
I continued on for several
years participating

01:31:40.590 --> 01:31:42.720 align:middle line:84%
in personal
development seminars,

01:31:42.720 --> 01:31:47.010 align:middle line:84%
and my life began to really
transform on many levels.

01:31:47.010 --> 01:31:50.940 align:middle line:84%
I had begun to love and
accept myself more in a way

01:31:50.940 --> 01:31:52.780 align:middle line:90%
that I never had before.

01:31:52.780 --> 01:31:55.650 align:middle line:84%
And from that new energy
that I was emanating,

01:31:55.650 --> 01:32:00.000 align:middle line:84%
I met a man that loved
me to the same degree

01:32:00.000 --> 01:32:03.150 align:middle line:84%
that I had finally
come to love myself.

01:32:03.150 --> 01:32:07.230 align:middle line:84%
He later became the love
of my life and my husband.

01:32:07.230 --> 01:32:09.450 align:middle line:84%
But from time to
time, depression still

01:32:09.450 --> 01:32:11.070 align:middle line:90%
overwhelmed me.

01:32:11.070 --> 01:32:13.860 align:middle line:84%
These times were
compounded by the thought,

01:32:13.860 --> 01:32:17.100 align:middle line:84%
after all the work I
have done on myself,

01:32:17.100 --> 01:32:19.020 align:middle line:90%
I'm back at square one.

01:32:19.020 --> 01:32:22.830 align:middle line:84%
In those times, it seemed
in vain and hopeless.

01:32:22.830 --> 01:32:25.020 align:middle line:84%
All along, my husband
Stuart could clearly

01:32:25.020 --> 01:32:27.270 align:middle line:84%
see that there was a
person inside of me that

01:32:27.270 --> 01:32:32.100 align:middle line:84%
was being extinguished by the
heavy medication that I was on.

01:32:32.100 --> 01:32:35.100 align:middle line:84%
He believed that my
only chance to enjoy

01:32:35.100 --> 01:32:38.850 align:middle line:84%
life and true happiness
was to come off medication.

01:32:38.850 --> 01:32:42.600 align:middle line:84%
And deep down, I
knew that was true.

01:32:42.600 --> 01:32:44.850 align:middle line:84%
I decided to try
coming off medication

01:32:44.850 --> 01:32:47.310 align:middle line:84%
and also decided that it
was important to do so

01:32:47.310 --> 01:32:48.820 align:middle line:90%
with support.

01:32:48.820 --> 01:32:50.400 align:middle line:84%
We went to Stuart's
doctor, who was

01:32:50.400 --> 01:32:52.710 align:middle line:84%
very supportive
about slowly reducing

01:32:52.710 --> 01:32:55.860 align:middle line:84%
the medication over
time, which, for me, was

01:32:55.860 --> 01:32:58.230 align:middle line:90%
an eight-month period.

01:32:58.230 --> 01:33:00.870 align:middle line:84%
In no way are we
suggesting that anyone

01:33:00.870 --> 01:33:03.060 align:middle line:90%
should come off medication.

01:33:03.060 --> 01:33:07.020 align:middle line:84%
We're simply sharing what
has worked for me personally,

01:33:07.020 --> 01:33:11.490 align:middle line:84%
and not everyone chooses the
conventional medicine path.

01:33:11.490 --> 01:33:14.160 align:middle line:84%
It was very important not
to come off medication

01:33:14.160 --> 01:33:18.900 align:middle line:84%
by myself without the guidance
of a supportive doctor

01:33:18.900 --> 01:33:22.950 align:middle line:84%
because they know more about the
effects of prescription drugs

01:33:22.950 --> 01:33:25.240 align:middle line:90%
than we do.

01:33:25.240 --> 01:33:29.200 align:middle line:84%
But the greatest support
of all came from Stuart.

01:33:29.200 --> 01:33:32.500 align:middle line:84%
I can not emphasize
enough how important

01:33:32.500 --> 01:33:35.920 align:middle line:84%
it is to have a support
person close to you that

01:33:35.920 --> 01:33:39.280 align:middle line:84%
becomes your voice of
reassurance and reason

01:33:39.280 --> 01:33:43.130 align:middle line:84%
when you experience
withdrawals or confusion.

01:33:43.130 --> 01:33:45.920 align:middle line:84%
There were moments
as I was withdrawing

01:33:45.920 --> 01:33:48.680 align:middle line:84%
that I thought I should go
back on medication because I

01:33:48.680 --> 01:33:50.900 align:middle line:90%
felt worse.

01:33:50.900 --> 01:33:54.350 align:middle line:84%
Stuart's voice
reassuring me that that

01:33:54.350 --> 01:33:56.750 align:middle line:84%
is a normal symptom
of withdrawal

01:33:56.750 --> 01:34:00.245 align:middle line:84%
and that it will pass was what
got me through to the end.

01:34:00.245 --> 01:34:03.010 align:middle line:90%


01:34:03.010 --> 01:34:06.610 align:middle line:84%
Years of medication had
wiped precious memories

01:34:06.610 --> 01:34:08.620 align:middle line:90%
of raising my children.

01:34:08.620 --> 01:34:10.720 align:middle line:84%
But for a time,
the medication was

01:34:10.720 --> 01:34:13.360 align:middle line:84%
what was needed in my
journey, as it showed me

01:34:13.360 --> 01:34:16.540 align:middle line:84%
the contrast of a
life half lived.

01:34:16.540 --> 01:34:19.060 align:middle line:84%
It taught me a great
deal about how much I

01:34:19.060 --> 01:34:23.170 align:middle line:84%
value the full array of
human feelings and emotions

01:34:23.170 --> 01:34:26.050 align:middle line:90%
in this experience called life.

01:34:26.050 --> 01:34:29.440 align:middle line:84%
We then came across the
work of Dr. Joe Dispenza,

01:34:29.440 --> 01:34:32.380 align:middle line:90%
and it really resonated with me.

01:34:32.380 --> 01:34:36.100 align:middle line:84%
I began to feel
excited by the prospect

01:34:36.100 --> 01:34:40.690 align:middle line:84%
that my mind, my
conditioning was changeable.

01:34:40.690 --> 01:34:44.470 align:middle line:84%
In scientific terms, it's
called neuroplasticity.

01:34:44.470 --> 01:34:47.020 align:middle line:84%
When I stopped to
consider this prospect,

01:34:47.020 --> 01:34:49.090 align:middle line:84%
I realized that my
mind had already

01:34:49.090 --> 01:34:52.060 align:middle line:84%
been changed so
profoundly about life

01:34:52.060 --> 01:34:54.770 align:middle line:84%
since I had begun
my healing journey.

01:34:54.770 --> 01:34:57.990 align:middle line:84%
But there were obviously
still some latent old beliefs

01:34:57.990 --> 01:34:59.770 align:middle line:84%
and conditioning
that I was still

01:34:59.770 --> 01:35:03.280 align:middle line:84%
buying into from time to
time that allowed depression

01:35:03.280 --> 01:35:06.400 align:middle line:84%
to sneak up on me
and pull me under.

01:35:06.400 --> 01:35:08.230 align:middle line:84%
Stuart recognized
and pointed out

01:35:08.230 --> 01:35:11.170 align:middle line:84%
that it mostly centered
around expectation--

01:35:11.170 --> 01:35:15.700 align:middle line:84%
expectations that I had of
myself that I continually felt

01:35:15.700 --> 01:35:18.160 align:middle line:90%
was unable to fulfill.

01:35:18.160 --> 01:35:20.990 align:middle line:84%
He totally hit the
nail on the head.

01:35:20.990 --> 01:35:23.770 align:middle line:84%
We both then went to some of
Dr. Joe Dispenza's seminars

01:35:23.770 --> 01:35:27.370 align:middle line:84%
that opened up our understanding
of the power of the mind,

01:35:27.370 --> 01:35:30.460 align:middle line:84%
and we began to
regularly meditate.

01:35:30.460 --> 01:35:34.480 align:middle line:84%
What this taught me was
the power of awareness.

01:35:34.480 --> 01:35:38.230 align:middle line:84%
I began to realize that my
thoughts and beliefs created

01:35:38.230 --> 01:35:40.690 align:middle line:90%
my subjective reality.

01:35:40.690 --> 01:35:44.560 align:middle line:84%
Thoughts have no power of their
own unless we believe them.

01:35:44.560 --> 01:35:48.970 align:middle line:84%
Over time, I began to recognize
the familiar unloving thoughts

01:35:48.970 --> 01:35:50.110 align:middle line:90%
as they arose.

01:35:50.110 --> 01:35:53.350 align:middle line:84%
And rather than automatically
believing and following them

01:35:53.350 --> 01:35:59.590 align:middle line:84%
as I had always done, I began
to ignore them out of existence.

01:35:59.590 --> 01:36:02.920 align:middle line:84%
A thought is just a thought,
but we automatically

01:36:02.920 --> 01:36:04.990 align:middle line:84%
grab hold of a
thought and follow it,

01:36:04.990 --> 01:36:08.020 align:middle line:84%
giving it its life through
the associated feelings

01:36:08.020 --> 01:36:10.660 align:middle line:84%
and emotions, which
then perpetuates

01:36:10.660 --> 01:36:12.880 align:middle line:84%
a cycle of feeling
the way we think

01:36:12.880 --> 01:36:15.460 align:middle line:90%
and thinking the way we feel.

01:36:15.460 --> 01:36:19.120 align:middle line:84%
The nature of the mind means
we can't stop or block thoughts

01:36:19.120 --> 01:36:23.770 align:middle line:84%
from coming, but we can develop
our awareness of thought

01:36:23.770 --> 01:36:27.460 align:middle line:84%
and choose to ignore the
ones that limit or hurt us,

01:36:27.460 --> 01:36:32.180 align:middle line:84%
which effectively pulls the
plug on their power over us.

01:36:32.180 --> 01:36:34.960 align:middle line:84%
I feel that it's no coincidence
that around this time,

01:36:34.960 --> 01:36:39.610 align:middle line:84%
we became ethical vegans after
watching a deeply distressing

01:36:39.610 --> 01:36:41.965 align:middle line:84%
exposé on the live
export industry.

01:36:41.965 --> 01:36:45.250 align:middle line:90%


01:36:45.250 --> 01:36:47.770 align:middle line:84%
When we became vegan,
we were immediately

01:36:47.770 --> 01:36:51.880 align:middle line:84%
concerned about ensuring that
we would get the right nutrition

01:36:51.880 --> 01:36:54.100 align:middle line:84%
because we'd been
brought up to believe

01:36:54.100 --> 01:36:56.140 align:middle line:84%
and conditioned to
believe that we needed

01:36:56.140 --> 01:37:00.970 align:middle line:84%
meat and dairy, particularly
for iron, protein, and calcium.

01:37:00.970 --> 01:37:04.330 align:middle line:84%
Thus began our
self-education and diet,

01:37:04.330 --> 01:37:08.770 align:middle line:84%
and its impact on our
physical and emotional health,

01:37:08.770 --> 01:37:13.240 align:middle line:84%
researching, watching DVDs
such as "Food Matters"; "Forks

01:37:13.240 --> 01:37:18.040 align:middle line:84%
Over Knives"; "Food That Kills";
"Fat, Sick and Nearly Dead";

01:37:18.040 --> 01:37:21.980 align:middle line:90%
"Simply Raw"; and many more.

01:37:21.980 --> 01:37:24.440 align:middle line:84%
What we also discovered
was that eating

01:37:24.440 --> 01:37:26.870 align:middle line:84%
nutritionally-dead,
processed foods

01:37:26.870 --> 01:37:29.870 align:middle line:84%
and also eating dead
animals takes away life

01:37:29.870 --> 01:37:32.210 align:middle line:84%
by promoting disease,
whereas eating

01:37:32.210 --> 01:37:36.380 align:middle line:84%
nutritionally-rich, living plant
foods that contain the Earth's

01:37:36.380 --> 01:37:39.470 align:middle line:84%
vital life force give
more life by helping

01:37:39.470 --> 01:37:42.800 align:middle line:90%
to prevent and reverse disease.

01:37:42.800 --> 01:37:46.130 align:middle line:84%
There is a significant
amount of our energy required

01:37:46.130 --> 01:37:49.940 align:middle line:84%
for the body to break down
the cooked deformed proteins

01:37:49.940 --> 01:37:52.310 align:middle line:84%
in meat, which is
completely devoid

01:37:52.310 --> 01:37:55.310 align:middle line:84%
of fiber, making it very
difficult for the body

01:37:55.310 --> 01:37:56.660 align:middle line:90%
to digest.

01:37:56.660 --> 01:38:01.790 align:middle line:84%
This energy could be freed up
as available energy for healing,

01:38:01.790 --> 01:38:04.670 align:middle line:90%
rather than used for digestion.

01:38:04.670 --> 01:38:08.100 align:middle line:84%
Animal products are also
inflammatory in the body.

01:38:08.100 --> 01:38:10.610 align:middle line:84%
In fact, it is now
commonly believed

01:38:10.610 --> 01:38:13.970 align:middle line:84%
that at the root of nearly
all disease is inflammation.

01:38:13.970 --> 01:38:16.660 align:middle line:90%


01:38:16.660 --> 01:38:19.460 align:middle line:84%
We also didn't realize
or think about the fact

01:38:19.460 --> 01:38:22.050 align:middle line:84%
that when an animal
is about to be killed,

01:38:22.050 --> 01:38:24.350 align:middle line:84%
it releases an enormous
amount of adrenaline

01:38:24.350 --> 01:38:26.570 align:middle line:84%
and cortisol into
its system as part

01:38:26.570 --> 01:38:28.880 align:middle line:84%
of the fight-and-flight
mechanism for survival

01:38:28.880 --> 01:38:30.470 align:middle line:90%
because it's afraid.

01:38:30.470 --> 01:38:32.390 align:middle line:84%
This adrenaline and
cortisol is then

01:38:32.390 --> 01:38:35.000 align:middle line:84%
consumed by us when
we eat its flesh,

01:38:35.000 --> 01:38:40.100 align:middle line:84%
and in my opinion, contributed
to my own anxiety levels.

01:38:40.100 --> 01:38:41.810 align:middle line:84%
We learned that
all dairy products

01:38:41.810 --> 01:38:45.110 align:middle line:84%
contain significant levels
of hormones such as estrogen

01:38:45.110 --> 01:38:46.790 align:middle line:84%
because in order
to produce milk,

01:38:46.790 --> 01:38:51.290 align:middle line:84%
cows need to be kept in almost
constant cycle of pregnancy.

01:38:51.290 --> 01:38:54.350 align:middle line:84%
Consuming these
hormones can interfere

01:38:54.350 --> 01:38:58.250 align:middle line:84%
with our body's own natural
hormonal balance, which,

01:38:58.250 --> 01:39:01.940 align:middle line:84%
in effect, could contribute
to fluctuations in mood,

01:39:01.940 --> 01:39:05.270 align:middle line:84%
among other serious
health issues associated

01:39:05.270 --> 01:39:08.690 align:middle line:84%
with consuming a substance
that is not meant for us.

01:39:08.690 --> 01:39:12.110 align:middle line:90%


01:39:12.110 --> 01:39:15.450 align:middle line:84%
Our concern about missing out on
nutrients in our new lifestyle

01:39:15.450 --> 01:39:20.040 align:middle line:84%
choice turned into inspiration
as we discovered testimonial

01:39:20.040 --> 01:39:23.340 align:middle line:84%
after testimonial of
people healing themselves

01:39:23.340 --> 01:39:25.290 align:middle line:84%
of major illness
through following

01:39:25.290 --> 01:39:27.540 align:middle line:90%
a whole food, plant-based diet.

01:39:27.540 --> 01:39:31.290 align:middle line:84%
And what was even more
exciting was the realization

01:39:31.290 --> 01:39:35.130 align:middle line:84%
that eating an abundance
of raw plant foods

01:39:35.130 --> 01:39:37.980 align:middle line:84%
could not only heal,
but help the body

01:39:37.980 --> 01:39:41.010 align:middle line:90%
to experience optimal health.

01:39:41.010 --> 01:39:44.700 align:middle line:84%
When I realized the potential
of this, I said to Stuart,

01:39:44.700 --> 01:39:48.090 align:middle line:84%
I want to know what
optimum health feels like.

01:39:48.090 --> 01:39:51.090 align:middle line:84%
I'm going raw for 30
days to see what happens.

01:39:51.090 --> 01:39:54.270 align:middle line:84%
And he immediately said
he wanted to join me.

01:39:54.270 --> 01:39:59.100 align:middle line:84%
A whole new world of how we
perceived food opened up.

01:39:59.100 --> 01:40:02.790 align:middle line:84%
It was intimidating and
exciting at the same time,

01:40:02.790 --> 01:40:05.970 align:middle line:84%
as we learned new
ways of preparing food

01:40:05.970 --> 01:40:08.850 align:middle line:84%
and experimented
with raw recipes.

01:40:08.850 --> 01:40:12.780 align:middle line:84%
We ate whatever fresh fruit
was in season for breakfast,

01:40:12.780 --> 01:40:16.320 align:middle line:84%
and apart from raw meals,
salads, and snacks,

01:40:16.320 --> 01:40:19.740 align:middle line:84%
we also juiced and
planted vegetables.

01:40:19.740 --> 01:40:21.900 align:middle line:84%
In the first couple
of days, we already

01:40:21.900 --> 01:40:24.570 align:middle line:84%
noticed that we felt
so much more energy

01:40:24.570 --> 01:40:29.400 align:middle line:84%
and had a natural, happy high
from the simple yet highly

01:40:29.400 --> 01:40:33.180 align:middle line:84%
nutritious living food that
we were putting into our body.

01:40:33.180 --> 01:40:35.580 align:middle line:84%
We both went through
some mild detox symptoms

01:40:35.580 --> 01:40:38.460 align:middle line:84%
in the beginning,
but they soon passed,

01:40:38.460 --> 01:40:41.910 align:middle line:84%
and we began to feel
strong and alive in a way

01:40:41.910 --> 01:40:44.940 align:middle line:84%
that we had not
experienced before.

01:40:44.940 --> 01:40:49.560 align:middle line:84%
I felt a new loving
connection and appreciation

01:40:49.560 --> 01:40:52.560 align:middle line:84%
of the vibrant food
from nature's garden

01:40:52.560 --> 01:40:55.650 align:middle line:84%
that I can only
describe as spiritual.

01:40:55.650 --> 01:40:58.860 align:middle line:84%
Of course, we both
lost unhealthy weight.

01:40:58.860 --> 01:41:01.470 align:middle line:84%
We had very regular
bowel movements.

01:41:01.470 --> 01:41:04.110 align:middle line:84%
Our skin changed,
and our energy levels

01:41:04.110 --> 01:41:07.230 align:middle line:84%
had increased so much that
our bodies were literally

01:41:07.230 --> 01:41:12.030 align:middle line:84%
asking for more exercise, which
is also key for depression.

01:41:12.030 --> 01:41:16.110 align:middle line:84%
One day, I ventured off on
our daily walk by myself,

01:41:16.110 --> 01:41:19.350 align:middle line:84%
and as I was walking,
something inside me

01:41:19.350 --> 01:41:22.860 align:middle line:90%
said run, run, just run.

01:41:22.860 --> 01:41:26.140 align:middle line:84%
So I broke into a jog,
and before I knew it,

01:41:26.140 --> 01:41:30.030 align:middle line:84%
I was running for the first
time since my teenage years.

01:41:30.030 --> 01:41:31.770 align:middle line:90%
It felt so good.

01:41:31.770 --> 01:41:35.790 align:middle line:84%
I felt so alive and free
of my chronic fatigue that

01:41:35.790 --> 01:41:38.640 align:middle line:90%
had plagued me for so long.

01:41:38.640 --> 01:41:42.270 align:middle line:84%
It's been many years now since
our raw for 30 days challenge,

01:41:42.270 --> 01:41:44.680 align:middle line:90%
and we have never looked back.

01:41:44.680 --> 01:41:46.980 align:middle line:84%
We're now eating a
high raw vegan diet

01:41:46.980 --> 01:41:49.110 align:middle line:84%
rather than 100%
raw, which we have

01:41:49.110 --> 01:41:52.790 align:middle line:84%
found more sustainable
for us in the long term.

01:41:52.790 --> 01:41:57.060 align:middle line:84%
But we were 100% raw whilst
our body was healing.

01:41:57.060 --> 01:42:00.660 align:middle line:84%
And you don't have to be all raw
to experience the huge health

01:42:00.660 --> 01:42:04.380 align:middle line:84%
benefits of switching to a
whole food, plant-based diet.

01:42:04.380 --> 01:42:06.480 align:middle line:84%
We also did a plant-based
nutrition course

01:42:06.480 --> 01:42:08.940 align:middle line:84%
so that we could further
integrate our knowledge

01:42:08.940 --> 01:42:12.810 align:middle line:84%
about nutrition and share what
we had learned and experienced

01:42:12.810 --> 01:42:15.840 align:middle line:90%
firsthand for ourselves.

01:42:15.840 --> 01:42:18.750 align:middle line:84%
Today, I am happier
and healthier

01:42:18.750 --> 01:42:20.910 align:middle line:90%
than I have ever been.

01:42:20.910 --> 01:42:23.670 align:middle line:84%
Yes, of course, I still
experience sadness sometimes,

01:42:23.670 --> 01:42:24.900 align:middle line:90%
like everyone else.

01:42:24.900 --> 01:42:28.230 align:middle line:84%
But rather than resisting these
emotions, which only creates

01:42:28.230 --> 01:42:31.890 align:middle line:84%
more suffering, I allow
them to come and go,

01:42:31.890 --> 01:42:34.410 align:middle line:90%
knowing that they are fleeting.

01:42:34.410 --> 01:42:38.700 align:middle line:84%
I realize that it is all part
of our dualistic existence,

01:42:38.700 --> 01:42:41.750 align:middle line:84%
such as happy and
sad, life and death,

01:42:41.750 --> 01:42:44.310 align:middle line:84%
and we can't have one
without the other.

01:42:44.310 --> 01:42:47.310 align:middle line:84%
Simply by putting
more life into my body

01:42:47.310 --> 01:42:49.790 align:middle line:84%
in the way of enzyme-rich
food and oxygen

01:42:49.790 --> 01:42:55.480 align:middle line:84%
through regular exercise, I
feel literally full of life.

01:42:55.480 --> 01:42:58.330 align:middle line:84%
We all have the power
to change ourselves.

01:42:58.330 --> 01:43:01.770 align:middle line:84%
And when we change,
life changes with us.

01:43:01.770 --> 01:43:04.590 align:middle line:84%
But it takes dropping
self-definitions

01:43:04.590 --> 01:43:06.300 align:middle line:90%
and expectations.

01:43:06.300 --> 01:43:09.690 align:middle line:84%
It takes realizing that
without sadness, we wouldn't

01:43:09.690 --> 01:43:11.640 align:middle line:90%
know what happiness is.

01:43:11.640 --> 01:43:13.950 align:middle line:84%
It takes recognizing
the blessings

01:43:13.950 --> 01:43:16.200 align:middle line:90%
amongst the pain of the past.

01:43:16.200 --> 01:43:19.320 align:middle line:84%
It takes letting go
and being vulnerable.

01:43:19.320 --> 01:43:23.220 align:middle line:84%
It takes opening up to new
ways of looking at things

01:43:23.220 --> 01:43:27.360 align:middle line:84%
rather than staying stuck in
what we think we already know.

01:43:27.360 --> 01:43:30.240 align:middle line:84%
It takes beginning
a new relationship

01:43:30.240 --> 01:43:34.320 align:middle line:84%
with food that is loving
and nourishing to us.

01:43:34.320 --> 01:43:39.210 align:middle line:84%
It takes the courage to
do whatever it takes.

01:43:39.210 --> 01:43:41.440 align:middle line:84%
Of course, not
everything can be healed,

01:43:41.440 --> 01:43:43.920 align:middle line:84%
as there are many factors
involved in the healing

01:43:43.920 --> 01:43:45.250 align:middle line:90%
process.

01:43:45.250 --> 01:43:48.270 align:middle line:84%
But we can certainly improve
the quality of our lives

01:43:48.270 --> 01:43:53.000 align:middle line:84%
just by making new, conscious
diet and lifestyle choices.

01:43:53.000 --> 01:43:57.250 align:middle line:84%
We both continue to
remain students of life.

01:43:57.250 --> 01:44:02.310 align:middle line:84%
Remember, nothing changes
until something changes.

01:44:02.310 --> 01:44:05.660 align:middle line:90%
